Reasoning: The paper discusses a tool for mechanically formalizing and verifying metatheoretic properties of programming language calculi, type systems, and operational semantics. This falls under the category of formal methods and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions nominal logic, which is a type of logic used in programming language theory and formal methods, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses techniques for model checking and counterexample generation, which are relevant to formal verification (cs.FL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
